.\" Man page for ocode serve
.TH OCODE-SERVE 1 "June 2025" "ocode" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ocode-serve \- Start the HTTP server with web UI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ocode serve
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Start the HTTP server that provides a web-based interface for ocode.
The server exposes REST API endpoints and serves the web UI.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-port\fR \fI<port>\fR
Port to listen on (default: 4096).
.TP
\fB\-host\fR \fI<host>\fR
Host to bind to (default: 0.0.0.0).
.TP
\fB\-open\fR
Open browser after starting.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show this help message and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
\fBOPENCODE_SERVER_USERNAME\fR
Basic auth username for the HTTP server.
.TP
\fBOPENCODE_SERVER_PASSWORD\fR
Basic auth password for the HTTP server.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start server on default port:
.B ocode serve
.TP
Start on custom port and open browser:
.B ocode serve -port 8080 -open
.TP
Bind to localhost only:
.B ocode serve -host 127.0.0.1 -port 3000
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ocode (1),
.BR ocode-web (1),
.BR ocode-run (1)